cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Communications / Networks: A Single-Axiom View of Shannon Theory, Internet, 5G/6G, Quantum Communication"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; current version
  v2.0.0 at 10.5281/zenodo.20133709) to communications and networks.
  Shannon's information theory is shown to be a special case of the
  ITU axiom delta_S = delta(K), with H(X) = (K)/ln2 and channel
  capacity = max modular K-flow. This is Tier 1 paper #14, opening
  the K-channel axis and bringing the ITU polytope to 14 vertices.
  Communications achieves degree 9, tying with Climate (#11) as the
  polytope's maximum-connectivity super-hub. Pass-1 progress: 98 of
  220 phases (44.5%).
  Phase 95 establishes the ITU foundation. Shannon H(X) = (K)/ln2 in
  ITU language. Internet traffic 2024 = 500 EB/month, doubling
  period 2.9 years, forecast 20,000 EB/mo by 2050 (40x growth).
  Mobile evolution 1G to 6G: bandwidth 2 kbps to 1 Tbps (5e8x),
  latency 1000 ms to 0.1 ms (1e4x improvement). Satellite
  constellations: 7,550 currently (Starlink 6,800, OneWeb 650),
  planned 60,506 total (8x expansion). Quantum communication
  (Micius satellite 1,200 km QKD) demonstrates ITU axiom realization
  in physical observable.
  Phase 96 details 6G, quantum internet, and federated learning.
  IMT-2030 (6G) targets: 1 Tbps peak (50x 5G), 10 Gbps user
  (100x), 0.1 ms latency (10x), 10^7 devices/km^2, 100x energy
  efficiency. Quantum Internet Wehner 2018 6-stage roadmap: Stage
  0-1 (trusted node, QKD) commercial 2024; Stage 2 (entanglement
  distribution) 2030; Stage 5 (distributed quantum computing) 2045.
  Federated Learning (McMahan 2017): centralized 0.994 acc, federated
  0.979 acc, local-only 0.698 acc — federated preserves privacy at
  minimal accuracy cost. Edge AI latency hierarchy: device 0.5 ms,
  6G edge 0.5 ms, regional DC 20 ms, cloud 80 ms, satellite 30 ms.
  Phase 97 covers industry, economy, and digital divide. Global ICT
  market: $5.3T (2024) → $30T (2050), Telecom subset $1.6T → $8T,
  AI subset $200B → $15T. Annual CapEx: $226B (2024, 5G dominant) →
  $655B (2050, Quantum $300B largest). Digital divide: world average
  62% (2024) with 3.17B offline → 93% (2050) with 0.65B offline (80%
  reduction). Sub-Saharan Africa 40% → 90%, LDCs 27% → 80%. 6G
  patents: China 40%, USA 35% (combined 75% — standardization war
  risk). Satellite geopolitics: Starlink (USA) 42,000 planned vs
  Guowang (China) 13,000 planned.
  Phase 98 synthesises the 2026-2050 roadmap with 16 milestones and
  10 falsifiable predictions (P_avg = 0.57). Key milestones: 2028
  IMT-2030 6G spec, 2030 6G commercial + Q-internet Stage 2, 2032
  Starlink 42K complete, 2035 Q-memory network, 2045 distributed
  Q-compute, 2050 99.5% global penetration. The ITU 14-vertex
  polytope completes with K-channel axis. Communications vertex
  bidirectionally connects to 9 other vertices (QC #1, AI #2,
  Crypto #3, Semi #4, Economics #8, Energy #10, Climate #11,
  Astrobiology #12, Robotics #13) — tying with Climate as the
  polytope's super-hub.
  Central thesis: communications is K-channel transport of
  K_information between subsystems. Shannon capacity = max modular
  K-flow makes communication engineering a direct application of
  ITU axiom. Quantum internet directly observes δS = δ⟨K⟩ through
  entanglement-based protocols. 6G + Quantum + Federated Learning
  forms a 3-layer K-flow architecture (classical channel + quantum
  state + distributed K_self) supporting Embodied AGI (Tier 1 #13).
  Pass-1 interpretive paper reframing Shannon (1948), Wehner (2018)
  quantum internet, McMahan (2017) federated learning, ITU-R
  IMT-2030 (2023), NIST PQC (2024), 3GPP Release 19 (2024), Pan
  Jianwei Micius (2017-2024), SpaceX Starlink, Amazon Kuiper, World
  Bank broadband economics, Gartner/IDC ICT forecasts in ITU
  language. Pass-2 follow-up would derive ITU-specific K-channel
  encoding schemes, novel quantum network latency bounds, K-flow
  federated learning optimization, and validation against real 6G
  deployments.
